@startuml
!theme plain
title PromptFlow React Streaming Chatbot - Component Diagram

package "Frontend Layer" {
    [React Application] as React
    [Chatbot Component] as Chatbot
    [Fetch API] as FetchAPI
}

package "Backend Layer" {
    [ASP.NET Core API] as WebAPI
    [ChatController] as Controller
    [HttpClient] as HttpClient
}

package "External Services" {
    [PromptFlow Service] as PromptFlow
    [Azure OpenAI] as OpenAI
}

package "Data Models" {
    [ChatRequest] as Request
    [ChatHistory] as History
    [ChatInput] as Input
    [ChatOutput] as Output
}

' Component relationships
React --> Chatbot : contains
Chatbot --> FetchAPI : uses
FetchAPI --> WebAPI : HTTP POST\n/api/Chat

WebAPI --> Controller : routes to
Controller --> HttpClient : uses
HttpClient --> PromptFlow : forwards request

PromptFlow --> OpenAI : processes via

Controller --> Request : receives
Request --> History : contains
History --> Input : has
History --> Output : has

' Interfaces
interface "REST API" as REST
interface "Server-Sent Events" as SSE
interface "Stream Processing" as Stream

FetchAPI --> REST
REST --> Controller
Controller --> SSE
SSE --> FetchAPI

Controller --> Stream
Stream --> HttpClient

note right of PromptFlow
  External AI service that
  processes chat requests
  and returns streaming responses
end note

note right of Controller
  Proxy component that:
  - Forwards requests to PromptFlow
  - Handles authentication
  - Streams responses back
end note

note right of Chatbot
  React component that:
  - Sends chat requests
  - Handles streaming responses
  - Updates UI in real-time
end note

@enduml